 Ulrich Mabunda (41) will appear in the Mpumalanga High Court today to appeal against the refusal to grant bail by the Nelspruit Magistrate’s Court on June 4. This is according to the spokeperson for the National Prosecuting Authority,  Monica Nyuswa. Ulrich faces charges of murder after he allegedly shot his 39-year-old wife, Tebogo, 10 times, killing her, before turning the gun on himself in an apparent attempt to end his life. The incident took place in Stonehenge on May 14. Lowvelder will publish updates as soon as more information becomes available. READ MORE: Bail denied in the Nelspruit Magistrate’s Court for suspect who allegedly kills wife 